HEADWORD: Fibrinoplastin
<hw>Fi`bri*no*plas"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Fibrin</ets> + Gr. <?/ to form, mold.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.Chem.)</fld> <def>An albuminous substance, existing in the
blood, which in combination with fibrinogen forms fibrin; -- called also
<altname>paraglobulin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fibrinous</ent>⟦br⟧
